name: ExtensionTerminologyCapabilities_CodeSystem
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `TerminologyCapabilities.codeSystem`, but has no comparisons.

element.short: A code system supported by the server
element.definition: Identifies a code system that is supported by the server. If there is a no code system URL, then this declares the general assumptions a client can make about support for any CodeSystem resource.
element.comment: The code system - identified by its system URL - may also be declared explicitly as a Code System Resource at /CodeSystem, but it might not be.
